North Manchester, Indiana, in Wabash county, is 34 miles W of Fort Wayne, Indiana and 87 miles N of Indianapolis, Indiana. There are an estimated 6,260 people in the town. North Manchester History. North Manchester was established in 1837. It was founded by Peter Ogan and named after Manchester, England. It is located on the Eel River in Wabash County, which was created in 1835 and named after the Wabash River. Wabash is the Miami Indian name for pure white.
